text: Adela Ana María del Rosario Camacho Sinibaldi de Torrebiarte (March 30, 1949 – December 15, 2020) was a Guatemalan politician. She was born in Guatemala City, Guatemala. She was a member of the Commitment, Renewal and Order. She was Minister of the Interior from 2007 to 2008. De Torrebiarte was President of the National Football Federation from 2016 to 2017. In 2020, she became a member of the Congress of the Republic of Guatemala. De Torrebiarte died of lung cancer in Guatemala City on 15 December 2020. ==References== Category:1949 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from lung cancer Category:Guatemalan politicians Category:People from Guatemala City
